
[1]noxious

   NOXIOUS, a. [L. from hurt.]

   1. Hurtful; harmful; baneful; pernicious; destructive; unwholesome;
   insalubrious; as noxious air, food, climate; pernicious; corrupting to
   morals; as noxious practices or examples; noxious haunts of vice.

   2. Guilty; criminal.

   Those who are noxious in the eye of the law. [Little used.]

   3. Unfavorable; injurious.

   Too frequent appearance in places of public resort is noxious to
   spiritual promotion.
